From: BCM6362 bringup <bringup@example.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH] b43: preserve silicon-default MultipleRead/Prefetch/BurstLen
 bits in DMA64 TXCTL programming

Symmetric to the previous patch that preserved silicon reset
defaults for the DMA64 RX engine. b43's dmacontroller_setup() TX
path writes TXCTL fresh from B43_DMA64_TXENABLE plus AddrExt and
ParityDisable, clobbering everything else.

Static audit of the proprietary wl blob (wlDSL-3580_EU.o_save,
SHA-256
a68a032673840c17a5981b0d00f16920ce992bca35ecdfba407bd6d488f28221)
shows dma_attach @0x13ed8..0x13f7c reads TXCTL four times at attach
time (while the register is at silicon reset value) and caches four
byte fields in the dma_info struct:

  pi->182 = (TXCTL >> 18) & 0x7   /* PrefetchThreshold */
  pi->183 = (TXCTL >>  6) & 0x3   /* MultipleRead      */
  pi->184 = (TXCTL >> 21) & 0x7   /* PrefetchControl   */
  pi->185 = (TXCTL >> 24) & 0x3   /* BurstLen          */

Then dma64_txinit @0x13434..0x13508 re-injects them on every TXCTL
programming via a mask-then-or sequence on each of the four ranges:

  v = (TXCTL & 0xffe3ffff) | (pi->182 << 18)   /* PT */
  v = (v     & 0xffffff3f) | (pi->183 <<  6)   /* MR */
  v = (v     & 0xff1fffff) | (pi->184 << 21)   /* PC */
  v = (v     & 0xfcffffff) | (pi->185 << 24)   /* BL */
  TXCTL = v

The four fields are silicon reset defaults; values differ by chip
and core revision. RX has three of them (no MultipleRead);
this patch adds the fourth.

For BCM4352 sitting on the BCM6362 PCIe RC, clobbering these to
zero leaves the TX DMA engine emitting inbound completion TLPs
with no prefetch, no multi-read on chained descriptors, and the
minimum burst length, which on this RC pairing contributes to
the same descriptor-fetch master-abort fault category as the RX
side (separately addressed by the previous patch).

This patch:
  1. Adds four register-field defines in dma.h
     (B43_DMA64_TXMULTIREAD_*, B43_DMA64_TXPREFTHRESH_*,
     B43_DMA64_TXPREFCTL_*, B43_DMA64_TXBURSTLEN_*).
  2. In dmacontroller_setup()'s DMA64 TX path, reads TXCTL first
     and ORs the four preserved fields into the new value,
     mirroring the OEM dma64_txinit phase-1 RMW. Reading once at
     setup is equivalent to the OEM's attach-time cache for the
     same reason as the RX patch: dmacontroller_setup runs after
     a fresh bcma core reset.

The OEM's two-phase write (config phase setting MR/PT/PC/BL with
XE still 0, then enable phase OR-ing in XE | maybe-PD) is collapsed
into b43's single write here. The end state is the same for a
clean post-reset engine; the silicon does not start fetching
descriptors before the descriptor pointers are programmed (which
happens after this write in dmacontroller_setup).

Tested on: D-Link DSL-3580L (BCM6362 SoC via bcma-host-soc, b43
phy0 and BCM4352 via BCM6362 PCIe RC, b43 phy1).

Signed-off-by: BCM6362 bringup <bringup@example.invalid>
---
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/b43/dma.h
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/b43/dma.h
@@ -88,6 +88,14 @@
 #define		B43_DMA64_TXLOOPBACK		0x00000004
 #define		B43_DMA64_TXFLUSH			0x00000010
 #define		B43_DMA64_TXPARITYDISABLE		0x00000800
+#define		B43_DMA64_TXMULTIREAD_MASK	0x000000C0
+#define		B43_DMA64_TXMULTIREAD_SHIFT	6
+#define		B43_DMA64_TXPREFTHRESH_MASK	0x001C0000
+#define		B43_DMA64_TXPREFTHRESH_SHIFT	18
+#define		B43_DMA64_TXPREFCTL_MASK		0x00E00000
+#define		B43_DMA64_TXPREFCTL_SHIFT	21
+#define		B43_DMA64_TXBURSTLEN_MASK	0x03000000
+#define		B43_DMA64_TXBURSTLEN_SHIFT	24
 #define		B43_DMA64_TXADDREXT_MASK		0x00030000
 #define		B43_DMA64_TXADDREXT_SHIFT		16
 #define B43_DMA64_TXINDEX				0x04
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/b43/dma.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/b43/dma.c
@@ -685,7 +685,30 @@
 			addrlo = b43_dma_address(&ring->dev->dma, ringbase, B43_DMA_ADDR_LOW);
 			addrhi = b43_dma_address(&ring->dev->dma, ringbase, B43_DMA_ADDR_HIGH);
 
-			value = B43_DMA64_TXENABLE;
+			/* Preserve silicon reset defaults for MultipleRead
+			 * (bits 6..7), PrefetchThreshold (bits 18..20),
+			 * PrefetchControl (bits 21..23) and BurstLen
+			 * (bits 24..25). The DSL-3580L OEM blob caches all
+			 * four at attach time in dma_attach
+			 * @0x13ed8..0x13f7c (TX) - symmetric to the RX
+			 * three-field cache the previous patch handled -
+			 * and re-injects them on every TXCTL programming
+			 * in dma64_txinit @0x13434..0x13508 via a
+			 * mask-then-or sequence on each of the four bit
+			 * ranges. RX has only three of these (no MR);
+			 * TX has the extra MultipleRead field at bits
+			 * 6..7 driven from pi->183. Reading once here is
+			 * equivalent to the OEM's attach-time cache for
+			 * the same reason the RX path uses it: dma-
+			 * controller_setup always runs while TXCTL is at
+			 * silicon reset defaults (just after a fresh
+			 * bcma core reset). */
+			value = b43_dma_read(ring, B43_DMA64_TXCTL) &
+				(B43_DMA64_TXMULTIREAD_MASK |
+				 B43_DMA64_TXPREFTHRESH_MASK |
+				 B43_DMA64_TXPREFCTL_MASK |
+				 B43_DMA64_TXBURSTLEN_MASK);
+			value |= B43_DMA64_TXENABLE;
 			value |= (addrext << B43_DMA64_TXADDREXT_SHIFT)
 			    & B43_DMA64_TXADDREXT_MASK;
 			if (!parity)
